Françoise Rosay https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fran%C3%A7oise_Rosay 0 Françoise Rosay (French: [ʁo.zɛ]; 19 April 1891 – 28 March 1974) was a French opera singer, diseuse, and actress who enjoyed a film career of over sixty years and who became a legendary figure in French cinema. She went on to appear in over 100 movies in her career.
